# Patch 0006 — Workspace templates (Kavacha Workspace Identities, Phase 2).
#
# What: one-click complete identities. "New Space from Template" in the
# create (+) menu offers Student / Developer / Private presets
# (KAVACHA_SPACE_TEMPLATES); each creates a space with its own dedicated
# Firefox container (created on demand, reused by name if it already
# exists), a template gradient theme, a search-engine override (Private →
# DuckDuckGo) and settings overrides (autoplay/notifications/passwords/
# suggestions per template). Space icons use Zen's selectable SVG set
# (school/code/lock-closed), no emoji. The space records template=<id> per
# the workspace schema. Extension recommendations are deferred until the
# marketplace can install them.
# Why a patch: composes the identity features from patches 0003–0005 with
# Zen's createAndSaveWorkspace() and ContextualIdentityService; everything
# applied on switch is handled by the hooks those patches added.
# Touches: src/zen/spaces/ZenSpaceManager.mjs,
#          src/browser/base/content/zen-panels/popups.inc,
#          locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-workspaces.ftl.
# Applies on top of 0005 (same files).
